{
  "texts": [
    "Section 2 discusses each of these challenges and provides research agendas around them.",
    "This includes developing methods and tools for selecting privacy parameters in a way that non-experts can easily understand and interact with the system.",
    "It also involves exposing well-documented implementations of DP algorithms, along with the chain of trust, for external scrutiny.",
    "This could potentially take the form of an open-source release of the implemented algorithm.",
    "Improving privacy/utility trade-offs: While DP has been used in several large-scale deployments (mentioned above), many of these deployments have ended up with privacy loss parameters that provide little if any meaningful privacy, and the challenge that comes with maintaining a high level of utility while preserving DP has limited its wider adoption."
  ]
}